<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Shadowbane, the first MMORPG (Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game) to include an integrated system for Strategic Warfare.<br>
<br>
Don't be too confused by the word 'Strategy.' What we're referring to is not a real-time strategy game, but rather a system for dealing with large groups of players. This means that we've incorporated many of the elements seen only in strategy games (like seiging cities, territory conquest, and tactical formations) on top of a great and fully-functional RPG. Players can still level and adventure as before, but we're extending the life of the game - adding a reason to continue playing once the RPG has been mastered.<br>
<br>
In a nutshell, we're expanding the concept of an Online persistent world RPG. Rather than focusing only on the story arc of the single character (and taking the game no further) we want to extend the experience by painting a backdrop of political unrest for players to become engrossed in.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
You can find the official FAQ <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.shadowbane.com/divination.shtml">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and a good unofficial one <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://sb.stratics.com/cgi-bin/faq_gen/index.shtml">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
You can find screenshots  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://shadowbane.godgames.com/sorcery/screenshots/index.shtml">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
You can find my &quot;Shadowbane versus DAoC&quot; <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/fdakorfrm7.showMessage?topicID=48.topic">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Beta status:<br>
Phase 1 has begun Feb 5th 2001. Phase 1 has 50 beta testers. There are currently about 2500 beta testers, who either signed up for beta in 1999 or registered on the official Shadowbane message board before May 5th, waiting to get into the following beta phases. At this point there is no information if there'll be an open beta phase. These 50 beta testers are employees of the producer, publishers and relatives. <br>
